# Web: SSR SEO (meta tags + JSON‑LD) for public routes

For SEO and link unfurls, ensure **all metadata is computed during SSR** (in `+page.server.ts`) and **rendered in the initial HTML**. The universal `+page.ts` and `+page.svelte` should *forward and render* the server results without recomputing them client-side.

This rule applies to:
- `web/src/routes/+page.*` (landing)
- `web/src/routes/(public)/pricing/*`
- `web/src/routes/(public)/blog/[slug]/*`
- `web/src/routes/(public)/p/[postId]/*`

Root layout SEO (`+layout.server.ts` → `baseMetaTags`, footer VMs) is separate; page loads merge `pageMetaTags` in `+layout.svelte` via `deepMerge(data.baseMetaTags, page.data.pageMetaTags)`.

---

## 1. SSR meta must be created in `+page.server.ts`

- **Set** `export const ssr = true;`.
- **Build meta via** `createMetaData(...) satisfies MetaTagsProps`.
- **Freeze** `pageMetaTags` and include a canonical fallback:
  - `canonical: new URL(url.pathname, url.origin).href`
  - then spread `...metaTags` (and `...baseMetaTags` on landing when extending layout meta)
- **Return** `pageMetaTags` from the server load so it exists on the first render (no JS required).

### Landing / pricing titles

- **Landing**: derive `customTitle` / `customDescription` from SSR `landing_page` config (`HERO_TITLE`, `HERO_SLOGAN`); collapse newlines in titles for the `<title>` tag. Merge OG/Twitter with `openGraphForPublicPage(customTitle, heroDescription, canonical)`.
- **Pricing**: use a fixed page title (e.g. `Pricing | {companyName}`) and a dedicated description string; pass `customSlug: 'pricing'`.

### Keywords (`customTags`)

- Prefer a dedicated `keywords` variable (array of strings) before calling `createMetaData`.
- Keep the array **stable and filter empty values**:
  - `.filter((t) => typeof t === 'string' && t.trim().length > 0)`

### OG image + Twitter card

If the page has a content-specific image, pass it via `customImages`:
- **Blog route**: build from `heroImageFilename` (inline blog image helper) and include `type` from a mime guess helper.
- **Preview route**: if there is post media, derive the public URL from the first `media[].path` (do not guess relative URLs).

When a content-specific image is present, also add a `twitter:card` override tag:
- `customMetaTags: [{ name: 'twitter:card', content: 'summary_large_image' }, ...]`

Notes:
- `createMetaData` already provides sane defaults (OG images and `twitter.cardType`), but **explicit `twitter:card` helps parity** with other public pages and avoids crawler quirks.

---

## 2. CMS copy must load on the server (landing + FAQ)

Public marketing copy that crawlers should index must not rely on client-only presenter state or in-component schema fallbacks alone.

- Load module config in `+page.server.ts` via `configRepository.getPublicModuleConfig(...)` (stateless; safe on server).
- Start from defaults helpers, then overlay API values when non-empty:
  - `getLandingPageConfigDefaults()` → `landingPageConfigVm` (`landing_page` module)
  - `getPublicFaqConfigDefaults()` → `publicFaqConfigVm` / `publicFaqConfigPm` (`public_faq` module)
- Return VMs from the server load; pass them through universal `+page.ts` and into templates (`LandingPage`, `PublicFaq`).
- **Landing FAQ headers**: prefer `landing_page` `FAQ_*` fields in the UI; use `public_faq` as fallback. **Pricing FAQ headers**: use `public_faq` only.
- Q&A item copy stays in `web/src/lib/content/constants/publicFaqCatalog.ts` (`PUBLIC_FAQ_ITEMS`); it is static and SSR-safe. Do not import `CONFIG_SCHEMA_*` in public UI for fallbacks when server loads already merge defaults — use `get*ConfigDefaults()` only as a last-resort in shared components.

---

## 3. JSON‑LD must render in `+page.svelte` `<svelte:head>`

- Compute structured data (JSON‑LD) in `+page.server.ts` (`schemaData`) and return it.
- Render it in `+page.svelte` so it appears in SSR HTML:

```svelte
<svelte:head>
  {#if schemaData}
    <script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify(schemaData)}</script>
  {/if}
</svelte:head>
```

Avoid:
- Generating JSON‑LD only in `onMount` (not SSR-visible).
- Putting JSON‑LD behind client-only conditions (`if (browser)`).

### Multiple types: use `@graph`

When a page exposes more than one schema type, return a single object:

```ts
const schemaData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    { '@type': 'WebSite', '@id': `${origin}/#website`, ... },
    createPublicFaqSEOSchema({ pageUrl: `${canonical}#faq`, name, description })
  ].filter((node) => Object.keys(node).length > 0)
};
```

Reference implementations:
- **Landing**: `WebSite` + `FAQPage`
- **Pricing**: `WebPage` (with `Offer` list) + `FAQPage`
- **Blog / post preview**: route-specific helpers (e.g. `createBlogPostSEOSchema`)

### FAQPage (`createPublicFaqSEOSchema`)

- Helper: `web/src/lib/content/utils/createPublicFaqSEOSchema.ts`
- Builds `FAQPage` with `mainEntity` → `Question` / `acceptedAnswer` → `Answer` (`text` must be plain text, matching visible accordion copy).
- Pass `pageUrl: `${canonical}#faq`` and the **same** section `name` / `description` shown in `PublicFaq`.
- Default `items` is `PUBLIC_FAQ_ITEMS`; only override when a route renders a different FAQ list.

### VideoObject (`createLandingDemoSEOSchema`)

- Helper: `web/src/lib/content/utils/createLandingDemoSEOSchema.ts`
- Builds `VideoObject` for the landing demo (`DEMO_YOUTUBE_VIDEO_ID`, `DEMO_TITLE`, `DEMO_DESCRIPTION` from SSR `landing_page` config).
- Include in landing `@graph` alongside `WebSite` and `FAQPage`.
- `HeroDemo` must expose crawlable demo URLs in SSR HTML: thumbnail `<img alt="…">`, `ExternalLink` to `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={id}`, and section `id="landing-demo"`.

---

## 4. Universal `+page.ts` must forward SSR meta + schema on client navigations

Client-side navigation (`goto`, clicking internal links) still needs correct meta/schema in page data.

- Follow the universal load pattern in `web-sveltekit-universal-page-load`:
  - `await parent()` first (auth state)
  - `if (browser && data)` return an explicit object that includes:
    - `pageMetaTags`
    - `schemaData`
    - SSR config VMs (`landingPageConfigVm`, `publicFaqConfigVm`, etc.)
    - route view models / arrays
    - accurate `isLoggedIn` (and `currentUser` / role flags if that route uses them)
- Do **not** recompute SEO meta in `+page.ts` on the client. Forward server output.

---

## 5. Canonical + slug hygiene

- `customSlug` passed to `createMetaData` must be a **path segment**, not a full URL.
- Use `encodeURIComponent` for dynamic path pieces.
- Prefer canonical derived from the request URL for SSR correctness:
  - `new URL(url.pathname, url.origin).href`
